<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFF96FF56FF4A8C0FE23EFC01" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FF96FF56FF4A8C0FE23EFC01" blockId="71.[151,1437,613,928]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9626913FF96FF56FF4A8C0FE670FCF6" bold="true" box="[199,314,829,855]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</emphasis>
Details of the rostral area are not described or illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FF96FF56FC5A8C0FE3CEFCF9" author="Barnard, J. L." box="[983,1156,829,856]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="73 - 115" refId="ref48311" refString="Barnard, J. L. (1962) Benthic marine Amphipoda of Southern California: families Tironidae to Gammaridae. Pacific Naturalist, 3, 73 - 115." type="journal article" year="1962">Barnard (1962)</bibRefCitation>
. The short, rounded front projection of the head and the slightly less than vertical, straight lateral front margin suggest the presence of a distinct rostrum hidden behind antenna 1. The species is otherwise in agreement with the present diagnosis of the genus.
</paragraph>
